        <num>65.501</num>
        <content>
          <p>As used in  to</p>
          <p>“Old revenues” shall be adjusted annually to incorporate the percentage change in the CPI. In the first calendar year of the calendar years described under , the calculated amount for the state tax revenues and the local tax revenues shall be adjusted by multiplying each amount by the percentage change in the CPI. For every calendar year thereafter until the expiration of the calendar years described under , the calculated amount for the state tax revenues and the local tax revenues shall be the previous year’s calculated amount multiplied by the percentage change in the CPI;</p>
